generationModele

Class Institution

  • java.lang.Object
    • generationModele.Institution

  • public class Institution
extends java.lang.Object
    Institution is a class which represents an institution.

    An institution consists of :

    • A name which is assigned at its creation.
    • A list of institutional paramaters.
    • A list of environnemental paramaters.

    It's possible to add parameters to or remove parameters from an institution .

      • addparameter

        public void addparameter(java.lang.String type,
                InstitutionalParameter parameter)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        Add a parameter to the institutional parameters hashMap or to the environnemental parameters hashMap.
        Parameters:
        type - Specify in which hashMap adding the parameter. Accepted strings : "institutional" or "environnement"
        parameter - The parameter to add.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Raise an exception if the type is different from "institutional" or from "environnement".
